{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-blog-template-js","path":"/linux/build-latest-meson-on-ubuntu-18","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"html":"<p>When I needed to build the latest <strong>plymouth</strong> for Ubuntu 18 I encountered a chain of problems preventing me doing it.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"text\"><pre class=\"language-text\"><code class=\"language-text\"></code></pre></div>\n<p>But nothing is impossible. Even ubiqutious Python we can update from 3.6 to 3.7 just to make meson happy.</p>\n<h2 id=\"update-python-from-36-to-37\" style=\"position:relative;\">Update Python from 3.6 to 3.7<a href=\"#update-python-from-36-to-37\" aria-label=\"update python from 36 to 37 permalink\" class=\"with-anchor after\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"20\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"20\">\n                <path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3\n                3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3\n                  9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64\n                  1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\">\n                </path>\n                </svg></a></h2>\n<p>Lukily there is a PPA for that</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"bash\"><pre class=\"language-bash\"><code class=\"language-bash\"><span class=\"token function\">apt</span> purge python\n<span class=\"token function\">apt</span> purge python3\n<span class=\"token function\">apt</span> <span class=\"token function\">install</span> software-properties-common\nadd-apt-repository ppa:deadsnakes/ppa\n<span class=\"token function\">apt</span> <span class=\"token function\">install</span> python3.7\nupdate-alternatives <span class=\"token parameter variable\">--install</span> /usr/bin/python3 python3 /usr/bin/python3.6 <span class=\"token number\">1</span>\nupdate-alternatives <span class=\"token parameter variable\">--install</span> /usr/bin/python3 python3 /usr/bin/python3.7 <span class=\"token number\">2</span>\npython3 <span class=\"token parameter variable\">--version</span></code></pre></div>\n<p>Then fix some things in the system</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"bash\"><pre class=\"language-bash\"><code class=\"language-bash\"><span class=\"token function\">nano</span> /usr/bin/gnome-terminal <span class=\"token comment\"># 3 -> 3.6</span>\n<span class=\"token builtin class-name\">cd</span> /usr/lib/python3/dist-packages/\n<span class=\"token function\">ln</span> <span class=\"token parameter variable\">-s</span> apt_pkg.cpython-36m-x86_64-linux-gnu.so apt_pkg.so</code></pre></div>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"bash\"><pre class=\"language-bash\"><code class=\"language-bash\"><span class=\"token function\">wget</span> https://github.com/ninja-build/ninja/releases/download/v1.11.1/ninja-linux.zip\n<span class=\"token function\">unzip</span> ninja-linux.zip <span class=\"token parameter variable\">-d</span> /usr/local/bin\n\n<span class=\"token function\">git</span> clone https://github.com/mesonbuild/meson.git /opt/meson\n<span class=\"token builtin class-name\">cd</span> /opt/meson\n<span class=\"token function\">wget</span> https://bootstrap.pypa.io/pip/pip.pyz\n\n<span class=\"token function\">apt-get</span> <span class=\"token function\">install</span> python3-setuptools\n<span class=\"token function\">curl</span> https://bootstrap.pypa.io/get-pip.py <span class=\"token parameter variable\">-o</span> get-pip.py\npython3.7 get-pip.py\n\npython3.7 <span class=\"token parameter variable\">-m</span> pip <span class=\"token function\">install</span> <span class=\"token parameter variable\">-e</span> /opt/meson</code></pre></div>\n<h2 id=\"other-dependencies\" style=\"position:relative;\">Other dependencies<a href=\"#other-dependencies\" aria-label=\"other dependencies permalink\" class=\"with-anchor after\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"20\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"20\">\n                <path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3\n                3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3\n                  9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64\n                  1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\">\n                </path>\n                </svg></a></h2>\n<p>Some dependencies are possible to get from the official repository</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"bash\"><pre class=\"language-bash\"><code class=\"language-bash\"><span class=\"token function\">apt</span> <span class=\"token function\">install</span> pkg-config <span class=\"token punctuation\">\\</span>\n  autoconf <span class=\"token punctuation\">\\</span>\n  libpng-dev <span class=\"token punctuation\">\\</span>\n  libpango1.0-dev <span class=\"token punctuation\">\\</span>\n  libdrm-dev <span class=\"token punctuation\">\\</span>\n  intltool <span class=\"token punctuation\">\\</span>\n  libudev-dev <span class=\"token punctuation\">\\</span>\n  libgtk-3-dev <span class=\"token punctuation\">\\</span>\n  xsltproc <span class=\"token punctuation\">\\</span>\n  libevdev-dev</code></pre></div>\n<p>But something like CMake provides a way to install the latest version</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"bash\"><pre class=\"language-bash\"><code class=\"language-bash\"><span class=\"token function\">apt</span> <span class=\"token function\">install</span> <span class=\"token function\">git</span>\n<span class=\"token function\">wget</span> https://github.com/Kitware/CMake/releases/download/v3.26.3/cmake-3.26.3-linux-x86_64.sh\n<span class=\"token function\">mkdir</span> /opt/cmake\n<span class=\"token function\">sh</span> cmake-3.26.3-linux-x86_64.sh <span class=\"token parameter variable\">--prefix</span><span class=\"token operator\">=</span>/opt/cmake --skip-license\n<span class=\"token function\">ln</span> <span class=\"token parameter variable\">-s</span> /opt/cmake/bin/cmake /usr/local/bin/cmake</code></pre></div>\n<h2 id=\"test\" style=\"position:relative;\">Test<a href=\"#test\" aria-label=\"test permalink\" class=\"with-anchor after\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"20\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"20\">\n                <path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3\n                3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3\n                  9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64\n                  1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\">\n                </path>\n                </svg></a></h2>\n<p>Let's test our fresh install of meson by building <a href=\"https://www.freedesktop.org/wiki/Software/Plymouth/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">plymouth</a> (sha: <code class=\"language-text\">a5eda165689864cc9a25ec14fd8c6da458598f42</code>)</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"bash\"><pre class=\"language-bash\"><code class=\"language-bash\"><span class=\"token function\">git</span> clone git://git.freedesktop.org/git/plymouth\n<span class=\"token builtin class-name\">cd</span> plymouth\n./autogen.sh <span class=\"token parameter variable\">--prefix</span><span class=\"token operator\">=</span>/usr <span class=\"token parameter variable\">--sysconfdir</span><span class=\"token operator\">=</span>/etc <span class=\"token parameter variable\">--localstatedir</span><span class=\"token operator\">=</span>/var --enable-tracing --disable-documentation\nmeson setup <span class=\"token punctuation\">\\</span>\n  <span class=\"token parameter variable\">--reconfigure</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">\\</span>\n  <span class=\"token parameter variable\">--prefix</span><span class=\"token operator\">=</span>/usr <span class=\"token punctuation\">\\</span>\n  <span class=\"token parameter variable\">--buildtype</span><span class=\"token operator\">=</span>plain <span class=\"token punctuation\">\\</span>\n  <span class=\"token parameter variable\">-D</span> <span class=\"token assign-left variable\">docs</span><span class=\"token operator\">=</span>false <span class=\"token punctuation\">\\</span>\n  <span class=\"token builtin class-name\">.</span> build\nmeson compile <span class=\"token parameter variable\">-C</span> build\nmeson <span class=\"token function\">install</span> <span class=\"token parameter variable\">-C</span> build <span class=\"token parameter variable\">--destdir</span> /opt/plymouth-bin</code></pre></div>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://aur.archlinux.org/cgit/aur.git/tree/PKGBUILD?h=plymouth-git\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">PKGBUILD</a> as an example build configuration</li>\n<li>And here's a <a href=\"https://gitlab.freedesktop.org/plymouth/plymouth/-/issues\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">list of current issues</a> in plymouth if there is something that bothers you and it's better be on the bleeding edge of development.</li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"references\" style=\"position:relative;\">References<a href=\"#references\" aria-label=\"references permalink\" class=\"with-anchor after\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"20\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"20\">\n                <path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3\n                3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3\n                  9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64\n                  1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\">\n                </path>\n                </svg></a></h2>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/mesonbuild/meson\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">meson build</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://pip.pypa.io/en/stable/installation/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">pip docs</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://stackoverflow.com/questions/54633657/how-to-install-pip-for-python-3-7-on-ubuntu-18\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">how to install pip</a></li>\n<li>module not found error for <a href=\"https://github.com/pypa/get-pip/issues/124\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">distutils</a></li>\n</ul>","excerpt":"When I needed to build the latest plymouth for Ubuntu 18 I encountered a chain of problems preventing me doing it. But nothing is impossible…","tableOfContents":"<ul>\n<li><a href=\"#update-python-from-36-to-37\">Update Python from 3.6 to 3.7</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#other-dependencies\">Other dependencies</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#test\">Test</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#references\">References</a></li>\n</ul>","frontmatter":{"date":"June 15, 2023","published":"June 15, 2023","lastModified":"June 15, 2023","title":"Build latest meson on Ubuntu 18","subtitle":"meson-0.61.5 and compile plymouth","section":null,"draft":null,"developing":null,"buttonText":null,"buttonLink":null,"secondButtonText":null,"secondButtonLink":null,"featuredImage":null}}},"pageContext":{"showLikes":true,"absolutePath":"/home/runner/work/mikolasan.github.io/mikolasan.github.io/src/markdown/linux/build-latest-meson-on-ubuntu-18.md","url":"/linux/build-latest-meson-on-ubuntu-18","next":{"excerpt":"What to build I build Lineage 15.1 from source. With some complications, but apparently it is possible and this inspired me to go further…","fileAbsolutePath":"/home/runner/work/mikolasan.github.io/mikolasan.github.io/src/markdown/linux/upgrad